<br>
*One person rounds them up and snares them as usual. <br>
*The other person does NOTHING while this is happening (any action deemed aggressive could split the crits up)<br>
*Once rounded up the second player runs up to the puller and then hits autofollow<br>
*The puller moves a safe distance and casts aoe dmg spell<br>
*Second person on autofollow waits for the puller to stop running and casts their aoe dmg spell.<br>
*Puller waits for second person to end cast and resumes kiting<br>
*At no point should the person on auto move off auto<br>
<br>
The 1st time I tried this it took a couple rounds to get it right. Once the timing was down it was a cake walk. The key is for the person on autofollow to start casting as soon as they see the puller stop and start to cast. That way both spells land almost at the same time and the puller isnt interuppting the followers spell by moving off. <br>
As the puller I would switch back and forth in overhead view to see when the follower stopped casting so I could immediatly move off (switching back to 1st person so I didnt run into anyone else). As the follower I stayed in 1st person view and watched nothing put the puller. That way I could time the spells right and trusted the puller on everything else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugvivis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gvivis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/01 7:26:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: quad spiroc at 48 with a fellow wiz</span><hr size=1> Nice, seem fun to try that out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uteranyon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teranyon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/01 6:55:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Solo from 48 - 51</span><hr size=1> Here's what I did, it just depends on the time of day and how crowded your server is.  Altho I prefer to group, I was naturally a little impatient to get IC, so I soloed when I got to 47.  From 47 to 49 I quadded bloodgills in Lake of Illomen.  It takes some practise, I died I think twice while learning the best way to do it.... Levitate is necessary, as is a good swim skill.  An FBE doesn't hurt either <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I managed to go from fresh 48 to 49 in 7 hours doing this, and I only had 2 of the dual spawns for most of that period.<br>
From 49 to 50, and even up to 51, I stayed in illomen when I wasn't grouped in ISK.  At this point, take the spawn at the ent to the underwater temple, where the marauder pops.  You can do this wheteher he's there or not.  Stay far enough back that you won't aggro the others, and open with IC, followed by Ice shock.  Few resists, and you can set it up so you med for like 3 minutes, nuke, loot, repeat.  An FBE is a requirement, really, to do this spawn.  The marauder is best kited when he's there, do it with FM, since he's got almost triple the normal bloodgill hp's.  The benefit of the marauder is you need his medallion for the VP key quest.  Good Luck.<br>
